File: Former Eskom CEO Brian Molefe has lost again. JOHANNESBURG - Former Transnet CEO, Brian Molefe has slammed the Zondo Commission accusing it of overlooking certain issues. Molefe took the stand soon after President Cyril Ramaphosa on Thursday. READ: State Capture | The money raised was never to buy votes - Ramaphosa "The other frustration is that this commission for example, it has chosen a particular narative and involvement in Transnet and Eskom and in not others," he said. "And I ask myself why these particular issues and these particular families, there are other families that also did things with these entities. There are other families who's behaviour qualifies with the definination of state capture." He however refused to answer questions relating to the testimony given by the estranged wife of former finance minister, Malusi Gigaba.